    "recap_headline": "University of Southern Mississippi Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BILOXI, Miss. \u2013\nEight different Southern Miss pitchers limited Nicholls to four hits as the No. 12 Golden Eagles blanked the Colonels 4-0 Tuesday night at Keesler Federal Park in front of 3,023.\nThe Golden Eagles (17-4) snapped a two-game losing streak to the Colonels (11-12) as they registered their second shutout of the season.\nDylan Causey\nstarted for the Golden Eagles and worked around two hits in his inning stint. He was then relieved by\nBruce Littleton\n,\nCamden Sunstrom\n,\nTeague Broadhead\n,\nJW Armistead\n,\nColby Allen\n,\nJosh Och\nand\nCamden Clark\nas the Colonels registered just five base runners after the first inning on two singles and three walks.\nLittleton walked a pair of hitters in the second and was relieved by Sunstrom who retired all eight batters he faced, which included three strikeouts, to earn the victory and improve to 2-1.\nThe Golden Eagles scored in each of the middle innings to pull ahead in the contest.\nBen Higdon\ndrove in the first run in the fourth on a sacrifice fly to the shortstop in short left field in the fourth to start the scoring.\nKyle Morrison\n, who was the only Golden Eagle with multiple hits collecting a pair of doubles, recorded an RBI two-base hit in the fifth, before\nSeth Smith\nknocked in a run on a fielder's choice in the sixth and\nGray Eubanks\ncompleted the scoring in the frame with a sacrifice fly.\nNicholls starter Dawson Richard (2-1) went five innings and allowed two runs (one earned) on three hits with two walks and four strikeouts to suffer the loss.\nThe Golden Eagles return to action Friday when they play host to Troy in the first of a three-game Sun Belt series at Pete Taylor Park/Hill Denson Field. Game time for the opener is 6 p.m."
  },
